Meteor is a full stack web application framework for,
Javascript, HTML/CSS with MongoDB as the backend. It was built for GridERP
but is pretty generic and can be used to build database driven apps.

The key difference in Meteor compared to other frameworks is that Meteor
is that meta-data is also treated as data and is used to build front-ends
very easily. Meteor comes with a full blown admin UI called the **Desk**
that handles forms, navigation, lists, menus, permissions, file attachment
and much more out of the box.

Meteor also has a plug-in architecture that can be used to build plugins
to GridERP.
